ABG.name: Customs decision request number

ABH.name: Sub-house bill of lading number
ABH.desc: Reference assigned to a sub-house bill of lading.

ABI.name: Deferred payment reference
ABI.desc: [1168] Reference or indication of the deferred payment of duty/tax.

ABJ.name: Quota number

ABP.name: Declarant's Customs identity number

ACC.name: Shipping unit identification
ACC.desc: Identifying marks on the outermost unit that is used to transport merchandise.

ACD.name: Additional reference number
ACD.desc: Reference number provided in addition to another given reference.

ACG.name: ATA carnet number

ACI.name: Outerpackaging unit identification
ACI.desc: (7070) Identifying marks on packing units contained within an outermost shipping unit.

ACJ.name: Customer material specification number

ACK.name: Bank reference

ACM.name: Unique REINAC reference number of the sender

ACN.name: Advice of collection number

ACP.name: Hot roll number

ACQ.name: Cold roll number

ACR.name: Railway wagon number

ACS.name: Unique CURRAC reference number of the sender

ACU.name: Loss/event number

ACW.desc: Reference number assigned to the message which was previously issued (e.g. in the case of a cancellation, the primary reference of the message to be cancelled will be quoted in this element).

ACX.name: Banker's acceptance
ACX.desc: Reference number for banker's acceptance issued by the accepting financial institution.

ADB.desc: Reference number for certificate of deposit allocated by issuing financial institution.

ADD.name: Analysis number/test number

AEA.name: Government agency reference number

AEE.name: Eur 1 certificate number

AEJ.name: Post-entry reference
AEJ.desc: Reference to a message related to a post-entry.

AEL.name: Delivery number (transport)
AEL.desc: Reference number by which a haulier/carrier will announce himself at the container terminal or depot when delivering equipment.

The same collecting points may be included in different transport routes, but in a different sequence.

AEN.name: Customer's unit inventory number
AEN.desc: Number assigned by customer to a unique unit for inventory purposes.

AEO.name: Product reservation number
AEO.desc: Number assigned by seller to identify reservation of specified products.

AEP.name: Project number
AEP.desc: Reference number assigned to a project.

AEQ.name: Drawing list number
AEQ.desc: Reference number identifying a drawing list.

AER.name: Project specification number
AER.desc: Reference number identifying a project specification.

AEU.name: Supplier's control number

AEV.name: Shipping note number
AEV.desc: Reference number assigned to a shipping note, see: 1001 = 630.

AEW.name: Empty container bill number
AEW.desc: Reference number assigned to an empty container bill, see: 1001 = 708.

AEX.name: Non-negotiable maritime transport document number
AEX.desc: Reference number assigned to a sea waybill, see: 1001 = 712.

AEY.name: Substitute air waybill number
AEY.desc: Reference number assigned to a substitute air waybill, see: 1001 = 743.

AEZ.name: Despatch note (post parcels) number
AEZ.desc: (1128) Reference number assigned to a despatch note (post parcels), see: 1001 = 750.

AF.name: Airlines flight identification number
AF.desc: (8110) Identification of a commercial flight by carrier code and number as assigned by the airline (IATA).

AFA.name: Through bill of lading number
AFA.desc: Reference number assigned to a through bill of lading, see: 1001 = 761.

AFB.name: Cargo manifest number
AFB.desc: Reference number assigned to a cargo manifest, see: 1001 = 785.

AFC.name: Bordereau number
AFC.desc: Reference number assigned to a bordereau, see: 1001 = 787.

AFD.name: Customs item number
AFD.desc: Number (1496 in CST) assigned by the declarant to an item.

AFE.name: Export Control Commodity number (ECCN)

AFF.name: Marking/label reference

AFI.name: Immediate transportation no. for in bond movement

AFS.name: Beneficiary's bank reference

AFT.name: Direct payment valuation number

AFU.desc: Reference number assigned to a direct payment valuation request.

AGC.name: Account party's bank reference
AGC.desc: Reference number of the account party's bank.

AGD.name: Agent's bank reference
AGD.desc: Reference number issued by the agent's bank.

AGG.name: Dispute number

AGH.name: Credit rating agency's reference number

AGN.name: Reference number quoted on statement

AGP.name: Company issued equipment ID

AGR.name: International flight number
AGR.desc: Airline flight number assigned to a flight originating and terminating across national borders.

AGS.name: Employer identification number of service bureau
AGS.desc: Reference number assigned by a service/processing bureau to an employer.

AGT.name: Service group identification number

AGU.name: Member number

AGX.desc: Reference number previously assigned to a service scheme or plan.

AGY.name: Receiving party's member identification
AGY.desc: Identification used by the receiving party for a member of a service scheme or group of persons.

AGZ.name: Payroll number

AHA.name: Packaging specification number

AHD.name: Fund code number

AHE.name: Signal code number

AHF.name: Major force program number

AHG.name: Nomination number

AHH.name: Laboratory registration number

AHI.name: Transport contract reference number
AHI.desc: Reference number of a transport contract.

AHJ.name: Payee's reference number

AHK.name: Payer's reference number

AHL.name: Creditor's reference number

AHM.name: Debtor's reference number

AHN.name: Joint venture reference number

AIA.name: Compliance code number

AIB.name: Department of transportation bond number

AID.name: Certificate of conformity

AIF.name: Previous delivery instruction number

AIK.name: Bank's individual transaction reference number
AIK.desc: Bank's reference number allocated by the bank to one specific transaction.

AIP.name: Customs preference inquiry number

AIR.name: Original certificate number

AIU.name: Charge card account number

AIW.name: Transport section reference number

AIX.name: Referred product for mechanical analysis

AIY.name: Referred product for chemical analysis
AIY.desc: A product number identifying the product which is used for chemical analysis considered valid for a group of products.

AU.name: Authorization to meet competition No.

AV.name: Account payable number

AWB.name: Air waybill number

BA.name: Beginning meter reading actual

BD.name: Bid number

BE.name: Beginning meter reading estimated

BT.name: Batch number/lot number

BW.name: Blended with number

CH.name: Customer catalog number

CM.name: Credit memo number

CMR.name: Road consignment note number
CMR.desc: Reference number assigned to a road consignment note, see: 1001 = 730.

CN.name: Carrier's reference number

CNO.name: Charge note reference number

CO.name: Buyers order number

CP.name: Condition of purchase document number

CR.name: Customer reference number

CRN.name: Conveyance reference number

CS.name: Condition of sale document number

CV.name: Container operators reference number

CW.name: Package number

DA.name: Deferment approval number

DAN.name: Debit account number

DB.name: Buyer's debtor number

EA.name: Ending meter reading actual

ED.name: Export declaration

MH.name: Manufacturing order number
MH.desc: Reference number assigned by manufacturer for a given production quantity of products.

MRN.name: Mailing reference number
MRN.desc: Identifies the party designated by the importer to receive certain customs correspondence in lieu of its being mailed directly to the importer.

MSS.name: Manufacturer's material safety data sheet number

MWB.name: Master air waybill number
MWB.desc: Reference number assigned to a master air waybill, see: 1001 = 741.

NA.name: North American hazardous goods classification number
NA.desc: Reference to materials designated as hazardous for purposes of transportation in North American commerce.

OH.name: Current invoice number
OH.desc: Reference number identifying the current invoice.

OI.name: Previous invoice number
OI.desc: Reference number identifying a previously issued invoice.

ON.name: Order number (purchase)
ON.desc: [1022] Reference number assigned by the buyer to an order.

OP.name: Original purchase order
OP.desc: Reference to the order previously sent.

OR.name: General order number
OR.desc: Customs number assigned to imported merchandise that has been left unclaimed and subsequently moved to a Customs bonded warehouse for storage.

PB.name: Payer's financial institution account number
PB.desc: Originated company account number (ACH transfer), check, draft or wire.

PC.name: Production code
PC.desc: Number assigned by the manufacturer to a specified article or batch to identify the manufacturing date etc. for subsequent reference.

PD.name: Promotion deal number
PD.desc: Number assigned by a vendor to a special promotion activity.

PF.name: Prime contractor contract number
PF.desc: Reference number assigned by the client to the contract of the prime contractor.

PK.name: Packing list number
PK.desc: (1014) Reference number assigned to a packing list, see: 1001 = 271.

PL.name: Price list number
PL.desc: Reference number assigned to a price list.

POR.name: Purchase order response number
POR.desc: Reference number assigned by the seller to an order response.

PP.name: Purchase order change number
PP.desc: Reference number assigned by a buyer for a revision of a purchase order.

PQ.name: Payment reference
PQ.desc: Reference number assigned to a payment.

PR.name: Price quote number
PR.desc: Reference number assigned by the seller to a quote.

PS.name: Purchase order number suffix
PS.desc: Purchase order number add on to split for detailed specification purposes.

PW.name: Prior purchase order number
PW.desc: Reference number of a purchase order previously sent to the supplier.

PY.name: Payee's financial institution account number
PY.desc: Receiving company account number (ACH transfer), check, draft or wire.

RC.name: Rail/road routing code
RC.desc: International Western and Eastern European route code used in all rail organizations and specified in the international tariffs (rail tariffs) known by the customers.

RCN.name: Railway consignment note number
RCN.desc: Reference number assigned to a rail consignment note, see: 1001 = 720.

RE.name: Release number
RE.desc: Reference number assigned to identify a release of a set of rules, conventions, conditions, etc.

REN.name: Received number
REN.desc: [1150] Number assigned to a rail consignment upon its arrival at its destination station (CIM 84).

RF.name: Export reference number
RF.desc: Reference number given to an export shipment.

RR.name: Payer's financial institution transit routing No.(ACH transfers)

RT.name: Payee's financial institution transit routing No.

SA.name: Sales person number
SA.desc: Identification number of a sales person.

SE.name: Serial number
SE.desc: Identification number of an item which distinguishes this specific item out of an number of identical items.

SH.name: Previous highest schedule number
SH.desc: Number of the latest schedule of a previous period (ODETTE DELINS).

SN.name: Seal number
SN.desc: [9308] Identification number on Customs or other seals affixed to containers or other transport units.

SRN.name: Shipment reference number
SRN.desc: [1140] Reference number assigned by a consignor to a particular shipment for his own purposes or for those of the consignee.

SS.name: Sellers reference number
SS.desc: Reference number assigned to a transaction by the seller.

STA.name: Station reference number
STA.desc: International UIC code assigned to every European rail station (CIM convention).

SW.name: Swap order number
SW.desc: Number assigned by the seller to a swap order (see definition of DE 1001, code 229).

SZ.name: Specification number
SZ.desc: Number assigned by the issuer to his specification.

TB.name: Trucker's bill of lading
TB.desc: A cargo list/description issued by a motor carrier of freight.

TE.name: Telex message number
TE.desc: Reference number identifying a telex message.

TF.name: Transfer number
TF.desc: An extra number assigned to goods or a container which functions as a reference number or as an authorization number to get the goods or container released from a certain party.

TI.name: TIR carnet number
TI.desc: Reference number assigned to a TIR carnet.

TL.name: Tax exemption licence number
TL.desc: Number assigned by the tax authorities to a party indicating its tax exemption authorization. This number could relate to a specified business type, a specified local area or a class of products.

TN.name: Transaction reference number
TN.desc: Reference applied to a transaction between two or more parties over a defined life cycle; e.g. number applied by importer or broker to obtain release from Customs, may then used to control declaration through final accounting (synonyms: declaration, entry number).

TP.name: Test report number
TP.desc: Reference number identifying a test report document relevant to the product.

UAR.name: Upper serial number of range
UAR.desc: Upper serial number in a range for declaration of incoming goods.

UC.name: Ultimate customer's reference number
UC.desc: The originator's reference number as forwarded in a sequence of parties involved.

UCN.name: Unique consignment reference number
UCN.desc: (1202) Unique reference of a consignment (UCRN) used for identification purposes in documents and messages exchanged between parties in international trade. See also: Unique Identifier Code (UNIC) in UN/ECE Recommendation No. 8, March 1992.

UN.name: United Nations dangerous goods (UNDG) number
UN.desc: [7124] Unique serial number assigned within the United Nations to substances and articles contained in a list of the dangerous goods most commonly carried.

UO.name: Ultimate customer's order number
UO.desc: The originator's order number as forwarded in a sequence of parties involved.

VA.name: VAT registration number
VA.desc: Unique number assigned by the relevant tax authority to identify a party for use in relation to Value Added Tax (VAT).

VC.name: Vendor contract number
VC.desc: Number assigned by the vendor to a contract.

VM.name: Vessel identification
VM.desc: (8123) Reference identifying a vessel (UN/ECE Recommendation No 10).

VN.name: Order number (vendor)
VN.desc: Reference number assigned by supplier to a buyer's purchase order.

VON.name: Voyage number
VON.desc: [8228] Reference number assigned by the carrier or his agent to the voyage of the vessel.

VP.name: Vendor product number
VP.desc: Number assigned by vendor to another manufacturer's product.

VT.name: Motor vehicle identification number
VT.desc: (Reference identifying a motor vehicle used for transport) normally is the vehicle registration number.

WE.name: Warehouse entry number
WE.desc: Entry number under which imported merchandise was placed in a Customs bonded warehouse.

XA.name: Company/place registration number
XA.desc: Company registration and place as legally required.

XC.name: Cargo control number
XC.desc: Reference used to identify and control a carrier and consignment from initial entry into a country until release of the cargo by Customs.

XP.name: Previous cargo control number
XP.desc: Where a consignment is deconsolidated and/or transferred to the control of another carrier or freight forwarder (e.g. housebill, abstract) this references the previous (e.g. master) cargo control number.
